<p>This document provides an overview of the neural network architectures u=
sed in GigaCheck for detecting LLM-generated content. GigaCheck employs a d=
ual-task architecture built on Mistral-7B that supports both document-level=
 classification and character-level detection of AI-generated text spans.</=
p>
<p>For detailed information on specific components, see:</p>
<ul>
<li>Mistral base model internals: <a href=3D"https://deepwiki.com/ai-foreve=
r/gigacheck/5.1-mistral-base-model" class=3D"text-neutral-300 hover:text-ne=
utral-200 hover:underline">Mistral Base Model</a></li>
<li>Classification head and LoRA configuration: <a href=3D"https://deepwiki=
.com/ai-forever/gigacheck/5.2-classification-head-and-lora" class=3D"text-n=
eutral-300 hover:text-neutral-200 hover:underline">Classification Head and =
LoRA</a></li>
<li>DETR detection system: <a href=3D"https://deepwiki.com/ai-forever/gigac=
heck/5.3-detr-detection-architecture" class=3D"text-neutral-300 hover:text-=
neutral-200 hover:underline">DETR Detection Architecture</a></li>
<li>Evaluation metrics implementation: <a href=3D"https://deepwiki.com/ai-f=
orever/gigacheck/5.4-metrics-and-evaluation" class=3D"text-neutral-300 hove=
r:text-neutral-200 hover:underline">Metrics and Evaluation</a></li>
</ul>
