sentation and passes it through a two-layer classification head:</p>
<p><strong>Classification Head Structure:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li><strong>Dropout Layer</strong>: Dropout rate from <code class=3D"rounde=
d-sm bg-[#e5e5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text-xs font-normal leading-[15=
px] before:hidden after:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]/30">config.classifier_drop=
out</code> (default 0.1)</li>
<li><strong>Dense Layer</strong>: <code class=3D"rounded-sm bg-[#e5e5e5] px=
-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text-xs font-normal leading-[15px] before:hidden af=
ter:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]/30">Linear(hidden_size=3D4096 =E2=86=92 4096)<=
/code> with tanh activation</li>
<li><strong>Dropout Layer</strong>: Same dropout rate</li>
<li><strong>Output Projection</strong>: <code class=3D"rounded-sm bg-[#e5e5=
e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text-xs font-normal leading-[15px] before:hid=
den after:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]/30">Linear(4096 =E2=86=92 num_labels)</c=
ode></li>
</ol>
<p>The <code class=3D"rounded-sm bg-[#e5e5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] tex=
t-xs font-normal leading-[15px] before:hidden after:hidden dark:bg-[#484848=
]/30">num_labels</code> parameter determines the classification task:</p>
<ul>
<li>Binary classification (human vs AI): <code class=3D"rounded-sm bg-[#e5e=
5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text-xs font-normal leading-[15px] before:hi=
dden after:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]/30">num_labels=3D2</code></li>
