<p>The model supports freezing the Mistral backbone for detection training,=
 which reduces memory requirements and focuses learning on the DETR compone=
nts:</p>
<p><strong>Freezing behavior:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>When <code class=3D"rounded-sm bg-[#e5e5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] t=
ext-xs font-normal leading-[15px] before:hidden after:hidden dark:bg-[#4848=
48]/30">freeze_backbone=3DTrue</code>, both <code class=3D"rounded-sm bg-[#=
e5e5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text-xs font-normal leading-[15px] before=
:hidden after:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]/30">model</code> (Mistral) and <code=
 class=3D"rounded-sm bg-[#e5e5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text-xs font-no=
rmal leading-[15px] before:hidden after:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]/30">classi=
fication_head</code> parameters are frozen</li>
<li>The frozen components are set to evaluation mode</li>
<li>Gradient computation is disabled for frozen parameters</li>
<li>This is typically used when training the detection head on top of a pre=
-trained classification model</li>
</ul>
