<p>The following design choices shape the model architecture:</p>
<ol>
<li><strong>Unified Model Class</strong>: Both tasks use the same <code cla=
ss=3D"rounded-sm bg-[#e5e5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text-xs font-normal=
 leading-[15px] before:hidden after:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]/30">MistralAID=
etectorForSequenceClassification</code> class with conditional branches rat=
her than separate model classes</li>
<li><strong>EOS Token Pooling</strong>: Classification uses the EOS token r=
epresentation rather than mean pooling or CLS token, suitable for causal la=
nguage models</li>
<li><strong>No Split Modules</strong>: The model defines <code class=3D"rou=
nded-sm bg-[#e5e5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text-xs font-normal leading-=
[15px] before:hidden after:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]/30">_no_split_modules</=
code> to prevent splitting specific layers across devices during distribute=
d training</li>
<li><strong>Flexible DETR Configuration</strong>: DETR parameters can be sp=
ecified at initialization or loaded from saved configs</li>
<li><strong>Optional Classification Head</strong>: The classification head =
can be set to <code class=3D"rounded-sm bg-[#e5e5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20r=
em] text-xs font-normal leading-[15px] before:hidden after:hidden dark:bg-[=
#484848]/30">None</code> when only detection output is needed</li>
<li><strong>Context Manager for Freezing</strong>: Uses <code class=3D"roun=
ded-sm bg-[#e5e5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text-xs font-normal leading-[=
15px] before:hidden after:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]/30">torch.no_grad()</cod=
e> or <code class=3D"rounded-sm bg-[#e5e5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text=
-xs font-normal leading-[15px] before:hidden after:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]=
/30">contextlib.nullcontext()</code> to conditionally disable gradients for=
 frozen backbone</li>
</ol>
